# aron (Accessible Repository On-demand Network)

## Introduction
**aron** is a platform that allows users to store and play media files (such as videos) on the web by simply entering a URL. As long as there is a network connection, users can easily access and play their media files at any time. The platform ensures seamless playback whenever you are online.

## Key Features
- Store media files (videos, etc.) on the web by entering a URL
- Play stored media files directly in the web browser
- (maybe) User-friendly interface for easy interaction

## Installation
1. Clone the repository.

    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/seolwu/aron.git
    ```

2. Install the dependencies. (Choose one of the following methods)
  
    **Using Yarn:**
    ```bash
    yarn install
    ```

    **Using pnpm:**
    ```bash
    pnpm install
    ```

3. Start the server:

    ```bash
    yarn start
    ```
    or
    ```bash
    pnpm start
    ```

